@startuml Connection Diagram for AI YouTube Summarizer

package "Client Side" {
    component "Chrome Extension" as Ext
    component "React Web App\n(port 3000)" as React
}

package "Server Side" {
    component "Flask Backend\n(port 5000)" as Flask
}

package "External Services" {
    component "YouTube API" as YT
    component "Hugging Face API" as HF
}

Ext --> Flask : HTTP requests\n(video URL)
React --> Flask : HTTP requests\n(text/PDF/URL)

Flask --> YT : Fetch transcript
Flask --> HF : Summarization & Translation

note right of Ext : Browser integration\nfor YouTube pages
note right of React : Standalone web interface
note right of Flask : Central server\nhandles AI processing
note right of YT : Provides video transcripts
note right of HF : AI models for\nsummarization & translation

@enduml
